{"name": "g2pkk", "metadata": {"name": "g2pkk", "version": "0.1.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Intended Audience :: Science/Research", "License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7"], "home_page": "https://github.com/harmlessman/g2pkk", "license": "Apache License 2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["jamo", "nltk"], "summary": "g2pkk: g2p module for Korean(cross platform)", "upload_time": 1662363156}, "documentation": ["# g2pkk\nThis is a cross-platform g2p for Korean.\n\ng2pkk is a library that made [Kyubyong's g2pk](https://github.com/Kyubyong/g2pK) work in Windows.\nThe reason why g2pk does not work well in Windows is that the `mecab`, the morpheme analyzer used by g2pk, causes build errors in Windows.\ng2pkk uses a different morpheme analyzer depending on the operating system.\nWindows uses [eunjeon](https://github.com/koshort/pyeunjeon), which enables mecab to be used in Windows, and other operating systems use [python-mecab-ko](https://github.com/jonghwanhyeon/python-mecab-ko), which was previously used in g2pk.\n\nInstall g2pkk and make sure that a morpheme analyzer exists for the operating system of the system you are using for the first time, and if not, proceed with the installation automatically.\n\n## Requirements\n* python >= 3.6\n* jamo\n* nltk\n\n\n## Installation\n```\npip install g2pkk\n```\n\n\n## How To Use\ng2pkk uses same syntaxes as g2pk.\n```\n>>> from g2pkk import G2p\n>>> g2p = G2p(\"\ud3ec\uc0c1\uc740 \uc5f4\uc2ec\ud788 \ud55c \uc544\uc774\uc5d0\uac8c\ub9cc \uc8fc\uc5b4\uc9c0\uae30 \ub54c\ubb38\uc5d0 \ud3ec\uc0c1\uc778 \uac83\uc785\ub2c8\ub2e4.\")\n>>> g2p(\"\ud3ec\uc0c1\uc73c \ub148\uc2ec\ud788 \ud558 \ub098\uc774\uc5d0\uac8c\ub9cc \uc8fc\uc5b4\uc9c0\uae30 \ub54c\ubb34\ub124 \ud3ec\uc0c1\uc778 \uac70\uc2ec\ub2c8\ub2e4.\")\n\n```\nIf you want more information, check [g2pk](https://github.com/Kyubyong/g2pK)\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "g2pkk.english", "documentation": ["Convert English to Hangul\nhttps://github.com/kyubyong/g2pK", "-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [{"name": "g2pkk.english.convert_eng", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "string", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cmu", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Convert a string such that English words inside are turned into Hangul.\nstring: input string.\ncmu: cmu dict object.\n\n```pycon\n>>> convert_eng(\"\uadf8 \uc0ac\ub78c \uc880 old school\uc774\uc57c\", cmu)\n\uadf8 \uc0ac\ub78c \uc880 \uc62c\ub4dc \uc2a4\ucfe8\uc774\uc57c\n```\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "g2pkk.english.cmu", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "g2pkk.g2pkk", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "g2pkk.g2pkk.g2p", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "g2pkk.g2pkk.G2p", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "g2pkk.g2pkk.G2p.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "g2pkk.g2pkk.G2p.load_module_func", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "module_name", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "g2pkk.g2pkk.G2p.check_mecab", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "g2pkk.g2pkk.G2p.get_mecab", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "g2pkk.g2pkk.G2p.idioms", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "string", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "descriptive", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Process each line in `idioms.txt`\nEach line is delimited by \"===\",\nand the left string is replaced by the right one.\ninp: input string.\ndescriptive: not used.\nverbose: boolean.\n\n```pycon\n>>> idioms(\"\uc9c0\uae08 mp3 \ud30c\uc77c\uc744 \ub2e4\uc6b4\ubc1b\uace0 \uc788\uc5b4\uc694\")\n\uc9c0\uae08 \uc5e0\ud53c\uc4f0\ub9ac \ud30c\uc77c\uc744 \ub2e4\uc6b4\ubc1b\uace0 \uc788\uc5b4\uc694\n```\n"]}, {"name": "g2pkk.g2pkk.G2p.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "string", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "descriptive", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "group_vowels", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "to_syl", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Main function\nstring: input string\ndescriptive: boolean.\nverbose: boolean\ngroup_vowels: boolean. If True, the vowels of the identical sound are normalized.\nto_syl: boolean. If True, hangul letters or jamo are assembled to form syllables.\n\nFor example, given an input string \"\ub098\uc758 \uce5c\uad6c\uac00 mp3 file 3\uac1c\ub97c \ub2e4\uc6b4\ubc1b\uace0 \uc788\ub2e4\",\nSTEP 1. idioms\n-> \ub098\uc758 \uce5c\uad6c\uac00 \uc5e0\ud53c\uc4f0\ub9ac file 3\uac1c\ub97c \ub2e4\uc6b4\ubc1b\uace0 \uc788\ub2e4\n\nSTEP 2. English to Hangul\n-> \ub098\uc758 \uce5c\uad6c\uac00 \uc5e0\ud53c\uc4f0\ub9ac \ud30c\uc77c 3\uac1c\ub97c \ub2e4\uc6b4\ubc1b\uace0 \uc788\ub2e4\n\nSTEP 3. annotate\n-> \ub098\uc758/J \uce5c\uad6c\uac00 \uc5e0\ud53c\uc4f0\ub9ac \ud30c\uc77c 3\uac1c/B\ub97c \ub2e4\uc6b4\ubc1b\uace0 \uc788\ub2e4\n\nSTEP 4. Spell out arabic numbers\n-> \ub098\uc758/J \uce5c\uad6c\uac00 \uc5e0\ud53c\uc4f0\ub9ac \ud30c\uc77c \uc138\uac1c/B\ub97c \ub2e4\uc6b4\ubc1b\uace0 \uc788\ub2e4\n\nSTEP 5. decompose\n-> \u1102\u1161\u110b\u1174/J \u110e\u1175\u11ab\u1100\u116e\u1100\u1161 \u110b\u1166\u11b7\u1111\u1175\u110a\u1173\u1105\u1175 \u1111\u1161\u110b\u1175\u11af \u1109\u1166\u1100\u1162/B\u1105\u1173\u11af \u1103\u1161\u110b\u116e\u11ab\u1107\u1161\u11ae\u1100\u1169 \u110b\u1175\u11bb\u1103\u1161\n\nSTEP 6-9. Hangul\n-> \ub098\uc758 \uce5c\uad6c\uac00 \uc5e0\ud53c\uc4f0\ub9ac \ud30c\uc77c \uc138\uac1c\ub97c \ub2e4\uc6b4\ubc1b\uaf2c \uc77b\ub530"]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "g2pkk.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "g2pkk.utils.adjust", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "arpabets", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Modify arpabets so that it fits our processes", "############# English ##############"]}, {"name": "g2pkk.utils.to_choseong", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "arpabet", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Arpabet to choseong or onset"]}, {"name": "g2pkk.utils.to_jungseong", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "arpabet", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Arpabet to jungseong or vowel"]}, {"name": "g2pkk.utils.to_jongseong", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "arpabet", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Arpabet to jongseong or coda"]}, {"name": "g2pkk.utils.reconstruct", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "string", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Some postprocessing rules"]}, {"name": "g2pkk.utils.parse_table", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Parse the main rule table", "############# Hangul ##############"]}, {"name": "g2pkk.utils.annotate", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "string", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mecab", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["############# Preprocessing ##############"]}, {"name": "g2pkk.utils.compose", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "letters", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["############# Postprocessing ##############"]}, {"name": "g2pkk.utils.group", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "inp", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["For group_vowels=True\nContemporarily, Korean speakers don't distinguish some vowels."]}, {"name": "g2pkk.utils._get_examples", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["For internal use"]}, {"name": "g2pkk.utils.get_rule_id2text", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["for verbose=True", "############# Utilities ##############"]}, {"name": "g2pkk.utils.gloss", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "out", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "inp", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "rule", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["displays the process and relevant information"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "g2pkk", "documentation": ["g2pK", "-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "g2pkk.absolute_import", "xref": {"fqname": "__future__.absolute_import", "project": null}}, {"name": "g2pkk.G2p", "xref": {"fqname": "g2pkk.g2pkk.G2p", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "g2pkk.regular", "documentation": ["https://github.com/kyubyong/g2pK", "-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [{"name": "g2pkk.regular.link1", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "inp", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "descriptive", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "g2pkk.regular.link2", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "inp", "type": null, "defa